key "ekblom2011applications,ellegren2014genome"
literal "false"

\end_inset

).
 Thus, the GWAS is becoming the standard tool to understand the genetic
 bases of either ecologically or economically relevant phenotypic variation
 for both model and non-model organisms.
 This increment includes complex species such as polyploids (Figure 
